NAME
    string-contains

DESCRIPTION
    Checks if a substring exists within a string, returning true or false.

    This function requires three parameters...
        @1 = substring (needle)
        @2 = string to search (haystack)

SYNOPSIS
    find-replace [NEEDLE] [HAYSTACK]

EXAMPLES
    if [[ "$(string-contains 'root' $PWD)" = "true" ]]; then
        echo 'case closed!'
    fi

    string-contains 'app' 'apple' # <- result/output is "true"

AVAILABLE OPTIONS:
    --help
